<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>LA grills run 12 months a year &mdash; and spiders treat every grill as a home</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Los Angeles is one of the few markets where gas grills are used year-round. That constant use means burner components wear faster than the national average &mdash; but it also means that when an LA homeowner fires up their grill after a two-week break, spiders and insects have moved in. Spider webs blocking burner ports and gas tubes are the most common cause of grill ignition failures in LA. The fix is cleaning, not parts.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first. The $89 fee covers the full assessment including gas supply check and post-repair leak test. If the grill just needs burner port cleaning, that&rsquo;s what you pay for &mdash; no fabricated parts cost. If an igniter module, regulator, or valve has actually failed, you get labor and the specific OEM part as two separate numbers before you approve anything.</p>
      <p>Luxury built-in grills are a significant part of our LA outdoor kitchen work. Lynx, Hestan, DCS, Kalamazoo, and Fire Magic grills in Brentwood, Pacific Palisades, and Encino outdoor kitchens see both regular use and coastal salt air corrosion. We assess built-in grills for corrosion and advise on maintenance to extend lifespan in these environments.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block">
      <div class="tip-label">&#128027; Spider season in LA &mdash; the #1 grill ignition cause</div>
      <p>Yellow sac spiders and black widows are common in LA backyards and love the enclosed spaces of grill burner tubes. A spider web blocking a burner port or venturi tube causes unlit gas buildup &mdash; a dangerous condition. If your grill won&rsquo;t ignite or has a yellow/orange flame, spider/insect nest clearing is the first step in every diagnosis. This often resolves the issue with no replacement part needed.</p>
    </div>

