    <h2>Questions about BBQ grill repair costs in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does BBQ grill repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor runs $120&ndash;$360 for standard brands. Igniter and burner cleaning &mdash; the most common calls &mdash; often require no replacement part. Parts are quoted separately. Lynx, Hestan, and luxury built-in grills run $240&ndash;$520+ in labor. The $89 diagnostic fee applies when you approve the repair.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why won&rsquo;t my gas grill ignite?</div><div class="faq-a">In Los Angeles, the most common cause is a spider or insect nest blocking the burner venturi tube or ports. This is a cleaning issue &mdash; not a parts failure. We check burner tubes before diagnosing igniter components. Many LA grill ignition calls resolve with cleaning and no replacement part.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">My grill has weak flame on all burners. Why?</div><div class="faq-a">Weak flame on all burners simultaneously is usually a regulator issue &mdash; either the regulator has failed or it&rsquo;s in safety lockout mode from the tank valve being opened too quickly. We test for lockout before recommending replacement. Lockout resets are free; only a failed regulator costs money for parts.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does Lynx or Hestan grill repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor for Lynx and Hestan grill repair runs $240&ndash;$520+ depending on the failure. These professional-grade built-in grills use proprietary burner systems and premium stainless components. Parts are quoted separately after diagnosis. Built-in grills in outdoor kitchens may require access work adding to labor.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; all prices on this page are labor only. Parts quoted separately after diagnosis. Gas pressure check and post-repair leak test included on every call. Coastal corrosion assessment included on outdoor grills. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the $89 diagnostic fee?</div><div class="faq-a">We charge $89 to come out and diagnose the problem, including burner port inspection, gas pressure check, and post-repair leak test. That fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work. If you decide not to repair, you pay $89 and we leave.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What warranty do you provide on BBQ grill repair?</div><div class="faq-a">90 days on parts and labor. Same issue within 90 days &mdash; we come back at no charge. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
